n=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of fear...</span><hr size=1> The thing wrong with most breaks is people not knowing where to go.  If you are taking many new people, I would recommend using 2 groups(people who know where to go or follow directions) to do initial break at west wall.  Have a druid in each group and evac if the cleric/chanters go down or if way too many mobs in camp. Rinse repeat.  Clear as many mobs as you can, then evac.  Clear the portal and west wall, then start bringing in the masses.  <br><br>Every failed break I have done was due to people running the wrong way from the portal then training camp.   This method should prevent that from occurring.   If the masses then run wrong way, you won;t have near the number of mobs to deal with.   <p>Vonson Ofabyatch---Bard of SZ<img src=http://forums.off-topic.net/images/smilies/greddy.gif><br><br>Baroness Kornaena D'Lez<img src=http://forums.off-topic.net/images/smilies/69.gif><br>Dark Elven <br>High Priestess<br>Mithaniel Marr<br> Unretired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF7D6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukendaien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kendaien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Knight<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#6C8361>(4/3/02 5:35:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=610.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of fear...</span><hr size=1> General rule of thumb:<br>West wall:<br>Single person who knows what they are doing running in: 0-1 adds<br>1 group of lvl 60ish people: 1-2 adds<br>3+ groups of people: 3+ adds<br><br>North wall:<br>Single person who knows what they are doing running in: 0-1 adds<br>1 group of lvl 60ish people: 2-4 adds<br>3+ groups of people: the entire fricking side of the zone.<br><br>North wall breaks, imho, are silly, slow, and unnecessary.<br>I actually agree with the origional poster, best break is a group of 6 who know what htey are doing hitting the west wall...then you can pull the portal area and the rest of the raid can waltz in in 10-20 minutes.<br><br>As for AE, well, it works, just has decently still class requirements...also, the ae groups had better be experienced.<br>But in general, it all depends on the classes you have available to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8Dc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/utksrelk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TKS Relk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/thekindredsouls/flag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#6C8361>(4/4/02 6:23:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=610.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of fear...</span><hr size=1> Hmm MOnk pops in flops the the floor looks around sees if thier are too many or not if thier are he gets up drags them away from zin and flops again, then in comes the druid he starts a slow moving train keeping them close by and away from other mobs, then we send in the mage, if the first two tactics didn't open it up enough the mage dies, this is called the mage sacrifice, yes it's a neccisary evil and works well /grins towards avalin (realy bro it's neccisary you get sacrificed 1-10 times a raid), if he dies druid or monk runs back and moves em again then group 1 comes in and Savaryen starts single pulling from the druids train (monkey still FD with mobs pokeing at him with a